name: PassThroughMBSIssueUnderwriter
definition: The party which agrees to buy any certificates that are not bought by investors Term origin:MBS PoC Reviews
label: pass through m b s issue underwriter

name: RealEstateMortgageInvestmentConduit
explanatoryNote: A real estate mortgage investment conduit may be organized as a partnership, a trust, a corporation, or an association and is exempt from federal taxes.
definition: special purpose vehicle that pools mortgage loans together and issues mortgage-backed securities
label: real estate mortgage investment conduit

name: MortgagePool
definition: loan pool consisting of mortgages that are held in trust as collateral for the issuance of a mortgage-backed security
label: mortgage pool

name: PassThroughMBSInstrument
label: pass through m b s instrument
definition: A security in which the cash flows from the underlying asset pool are passed through to the investor by way of redemption payments.

name: MortgageBackedSecurity
definition: debt obligations that represent claims to the cash flows from pools of mortgage loans, most commonly on residential property
label: mortgage-backed security
explanatoryNote: Mortgage loans are purchased from banks, mortgage companies and other originators, and then assembled into pools by a governmental, quasigovernmental or private entity. The entity then issues securities that represent claims on the principal and interest payments made by borrowers on the loans in the pool, a process known as securitization.

name: AgencyMBSPool
label: agency m b s pool
definition: A pool investment consisting of a collection of Agency MBS instruments.
explanatoryNote: This pool may be used as the underlying for an agency CMO. Non agency CMOs do not exist.

name: MBSPool
definition: A pool investment consisting of a collection of MBS instruments.
label: m b s pool

name: AgencyMBSIssuer
label: agency m b s issuer
definition: The issuer of the pass through MBS is an Agency issuer. This is identified as being some kind of agency that is set up specifically to issue these instruments.

name: MBSIssuer
label: m b s issuer
definition: The issuer of a Mortgage Backed Security.
explanatoryNote: This can be an agency that exists for this purpose or it may be the issuer of the original mortgages in the pool.

name: GovernmentMortgageAgency
label: government mortgage agency
definition: An agency set up by a government for the purpose of issuing mortgages.

name: MortgageBackedSecurityOfferingProspectus
definition: Prospectus describing the terms of the issue and each of the instruments included in the mortgage backed security issue. Term origin:SMER
label: mortgage-backed security offering prospectus

name: AgencyMortgagePool
definition: A pool of agency mortgages.
label: agency mortgage pool

name: PassThroughMBSDeal
label: pass through m b s deal
definition: An issue of Mortgage Backed Security instruments in which payments on the pool are passed through to investors

name: PassThroughMBSInstrumentNote
definition: An individual note of a pass through instrument.
label: pass through m b s instrument note

name: IssuedAndSecuritizedNonAgencyMortgagePool
definition: A non agency mortgage pool which has been securitized as part of a tranched Mortgage Backed Security.
label: issued and securitized non agency mortgage pool

name: AgencyMBSDeal
definition: An issue of securities backed by pools of mortgages held by government agencies.
label: agency m b s deal
explanatoryNote: These are Ginnie Mae, Freddie Mac and Fannie Mae (for the US). Of these agencies, GNMA (Ginnie Mae) issues mortgages in its own right (Investorwords differs on this). Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac purchase mortgages. Those mortgages are issued by banks. Before one of these agencies purchases a mortgage, there are certain criteria that have to be met. These are specified in terms of, for example, the balance of the mortgage, limits to credit ratings.

name: PrivateLabelMBSDeal
label: private label m b s deal

name: NonAgencyMBSIssuer
definition: A party which is a non agency issuer of MBS securities. The identity of this party may be a bank or a specialist (non agency) mortgage company. Term origin:MBS PoC Reviews
label: non agency m b s issuer

name: PassThroughMBSDealProspectus
definition: The written prospectus for an agency, pass through issue of Mortgage Backed Securities
label: pass through m b s deal prospectus

name: ResidentialMBS
explanatoryNote: Notes from CESR: They are issued by banks and backed by an underlying pool of residential mortgages. There can be some distinctions between prime RMBS and sub-prime/non-conforming RMBS although there is no consensus about what constitutes a sub-prime/non-conforming mortgage in Europe.
definition: Residential Mortgage-Backed Securities, which are trust certificates (bonds) backed by a pool of residential mortgage loans.
label: residential m b s

name: IssuedAndSecuritizedAgencyMortagePool
label: issued and securitized agency mortage pool
definition: An agency mortgage pool which has been securitized as part of an agency Mortgage Backed Security.

name: SpecialistMortgageIssuer
definition: A business organization that specialises in and exists for the issuance of mortgages to the general public.
label: specialist mortgage issuer

name: denomination.1
definition: The currency amount in which the Note is denominated, for example $500 notes. This term added by symmettry with MBS Tranche Note. needs to be reviewed and validated.
label: denomination

name: prime
definition: Whether the mortage pool is identified as Prime or not.
label: prime
